author: Written by: Sam Winstrom, Assignment Editor
title: NOPD: Suspect arrested in attempted rape of teenager
text:
NEW ORLEANS (WVUE) - Police made an arrest in the case of the attempted sexual assault of a 14-year-old girl.
According to NOPD, the Violent Offenders Warrant Squad arrested 29-year-old Kevin Herring as a suspect in the attempted sexual assault reported in New Orleans East.
A 14-year-old girl told detectives that Herring forced her inside her home and attempted to sexually assaulted her on the afternoon of Sept. 16. Police say Herring was developed as a suspect through further investigation, leading to his arrest.
Herring was arrested and booked today, Oct. 7, for Attempted Aggravated Rape.
